obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2907)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2907&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Bureau of Indian`
  line `Standards Act, 2016.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 12th October 2017, vide Notification No. S.O.3295(E) dated 12th October 2017, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `Section 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2908)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2908&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(1) “article” means any substance, artificial or natural, or partly artificial or partly natural,`
  line `whether raw or partly or wholly processed or manufactured or handmade within India or imported`
  line `into India;`
  line
  line `(2) “assaying and hallmarking centre” means a testing and marking centre recognised by the`
  line `Bureau to determine the purity of precious metal articles and to apply hallmark on the precious metal`
  line `articles in a manner as may be determined by regulations;`
  line
  line `(3) “Bureau” means the Bureau of Indian Standards established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(4) “certification officer” means a certification officer appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 27;`
  line
  line `(5) “certified body” means a holder of certificate of conformity or licence under sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 13 in relation to any goods, article, process, system or service which conforms to a`
  line standard;
  line
  line `(6) “certified jeweller” means a jeweller who has been granted a certificate by the Bureau to get`
  line `manufactured for sale or to sell any precious metal article after getting the same hallmarked in a`
  line `manner as may be determined by regulations;`
  line
  line `(7) “conformity assessment” means demonstration that requirements as may be specified relating`
  line `to an article, process, system, service, person or body are fulfilled;`
  line
  line `(8) “conformity assessment scheme” means a scheme relating to such goods, article, process,`
  line `system or service as may be notified by the Bureau under section 12;`
  line
  line `(9) “consumer” means a person as defined in the Consumer Protection Act, 1986 (68 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(10) “covering” includes any stopper, cask, bottle, vessel, box, crate, cover, capsule, case, frame,`
  line `wrapper, bag, sack, pouch or other container;`
  line
  line `(11) “Director General” means the Director General appointed under sub-section (1) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(12) “Executive Committee” means the Executive Committee constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4;`
  line
  line `(13) “fund” means the fund constituted under section 20;`
  line
  line `(14) “goods” includes all kinds of movable properties under the Sale of Goods`
  line `Act, 1930 (3 of 1930), other than actionable claims, money, stocks and shares;`
  line
  line `(15) “Governing Council” means a Governing Council constituted under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(16) “Hallmark” means in relation to precious metal article, the Standard Mark, which indicates`
  line `the proportionate content of precious metal in that article as per the relevant Indian Standard;`
  line
  line `(17) “Indian Standard” means the standard including any tentative or provisional standard`
  line `established and published by the Bureau, in relation to any goods, article, process, system or service,`
  line `indicative of the quality and specification of such goods, article, process, system or service and`
  line includes—
  line
  line `(i) any standard adopted by the Bureau under sub-section (2) of section 10; and`
  line
  line `(ii) any standard established and published, or recognised, by the Bureau of Indian Standards`
  line `established under the Bureau of Indian Standard Act, 1986 (63 of 1986), which was in force`
  line `immediately before the commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(18) “Indian Standards Institution” means the Indian Standards Institution registered under the`
  line `Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(19) “jeweller” means a person engaged in the business to get manufactured precious metal article`
  line `for sale or to sell precious metal articles;`
  line
  line `(20) “licence” means a licence granted under section 13 to use a specified Standard Mark in`
  line `relation to any goods, article, process, system or service, which conforms to a standard;`
  line
  line `(21) “manufacturer” means a person responsible for designing and manufacturing any goods or`
  line article;
  line
  line `(22) “mark” includes a device, brand, heading, label, ticket, pictorial representation, name,`
  line `signature, word, letter or numeral or any combination thereof;`
  line
  line `(23) “member” means a member of the Governing Council, Executive Committee or any of the`
  line `Advisory Committee;`
  line
  line `(24) “notification” means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `“notify” or “notified” shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(25) “person” means a manufacturer, an importer, a distributor, retailer, seller or lessor of goods`
  line `or article or provider of service or any other person who uses or applies his name or trade mark or any`
  line `other distinctive mark on to goods or article or while providing a service, for any consideration or`
  line `gives goods or article or provides service as prize or gift for commercial purposes including their`
  line `representative and any person who is engaged in such activities, where the manufacturer, importer,`
  line `distributor, retailer, seller, lessor or provider of service cannot be identified;`
  line
  line `(26) “precious metal” means gold, silver, platinum and palladium;`
  line
  line `(27) “precious metal article” means any article made entirely or in part from precious metals or`
  line `their alloys;`
  line
  line `(28) “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(29) “process” means a set of inter-related or interacting activities, which transforms inputs into`
  line outputs;
  line
  line `(30) “recognised testing and marking centre” means a testing and marking centre recognised by`
  line `the Bureau under sub-section (5) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(31) “recognised testing laboratory” means a testing laboratory recognised by the Bureau under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(32) “registering authority” means any authority competent under any law for the time being in`
  line `force to register any company, firm or other body of persons, or any trade mark or design, or to grant`
  line `a patent;`
  line
  line `(33) “regulations” means regulations made by the Bureau under this Act;`
  line
  line `(34) “sale” means to sell, distribute, hire, lease or exchange of goods, article, process, system or`
  line `service for any consideration or for commercial purposes;`
  line
  line `(35) “seller” means a person who is engaged in the sale of any goods, article, process, system or`
  line service;
  line
  line `(36) “service” means the result generated by activities at the interface between an organisation`
  line `and a customer and by organisation’s internal activities, to meet customer requirements;`
  line
  line `(37) “specification” means a description of goods, article, process, system or service as far as`
  line `practicable by reference to its nature, quality, strength, purity, composition, quantity, dimensions,`
  line `weight, grade, durability, origin, age, material, mode of manufacture or processing, consistency and`
  line `reliability of service delivery or other characteristics to distinguish it from any other goods, article,`
  line `process, system or service;`
  line
  line `(38) “specified” means specified by the regulations;`
  line
  line `(39) “standards” means documented agreements containing technical specifications or other`
  line `precise criteria to be used consistently as rules, guidelines, or definitions of characteristics, to ensure`
  line `that goods, articles, processes, systems and services are fit for their purpose;`
  line
  line `(40) “Standard Mark” means the mark specified by the Bureau, and includes Hallmark, to`
  line `represent conformity of goods, article, process, system or service to a particular Indian Standard or`
  line `conformity to a standard, the mark of which has been established, adopted or recognised by the`
  line `Bureau and is marked on the article or goods as a Standard Mark or on its covering or label attached`
  line `to such goods or article so marked;`
  line
  line `(41) “system” means a set of inter-related or interacting elements;`
  line
  line `(42) “testing laboratory” means a body set up for the purpose of testing of goods or article against`
  line `a set of requirements and report its findings;`
  line
  line `(43) “trade mark” means a mark used or proposed to be used in relation to goods or article or`
  line `process or system or service for the purpose of indicating, or so as to indicate, a connection in the`
  line `course of trade of goods, article, process, system or service, as the case may be, and some person`
  line `having the right, either as proprietor or as registered user, to use the mark, whether with or without`
  line `any indication of the identity of that person.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2909)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Bureau and Constitution of Governing Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2909&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such`
  line `date as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf, there`
  line `shall be established a national body for the purposes of this Act, a Bureau, to be called the Bureau of`
  line `Indian Standards.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bureau shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property,`
  line `both movable and immovable, and to contract and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The members of the Governing Council shall constitute the Bureau and general superintendence,`
  line `direction and management of the affairs of the Bureau shall vest in the Governing Council, which shall`
  line `consist of the following members, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the Minister in-charge of the Ministry or Department of the Central Government having`
  line `administrative control of the Bureau who shall be ex officio President of the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(b) the Minister of State or a Deputy Minister, if any, in the Ministry or Department of the`
  line `Central Government having administrative control of the Bureau who shall be ex officio`
  line `Vice-President of the Bureau, and where there is no such Minister of State or Deputy Minister, such`
  line `person as may be nominated by the Central Government to be the Vice-President of the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(c) the Secretary to the Government of India of the Ministry or Department of the Central`
  line `Government having administrative control of the Bureau, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Director General of the Bureau, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) such number of other persons to represent the Government, industry, scientific and research`
  line `institutions, consumers and other interests, as may be prescribed, to be appointed by the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of the members referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (3) and the manner of`
  line `filling vacancies among, and the procedure to be followed in the discharge of their functions by the`
  line `members, shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member, other than an ex officio member of the Bureau of Indian Standards`
  line `constituted under the Bureau of Indian Standards Act, 1986 (63 of 1986), shall, after the commencement`
  line `of this Act, continue to hold such office as member till the completion of his term`
  line
  line `(5) The Governing Council may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be`
  line `prescribed, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire in complying with any of the provisions`
  line `of this Act and a person so associated shall have the right to take part in the discussions of the Governing`
  line `Council relevant to the purposes for which he has been associated but shall not have the right to vote.`
  line
  line `(6) The Governing Council may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to any member, the`
  line `Director General or any other person subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order,`
  line `such of its powers and functions under this Act except the powers under section 37 as it may deem`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2910)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Executive Committee of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2910&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Governing Council may, with the prior approval of`
  line `the Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute an Executive Committee which`
  line `shall consist of the following members, namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) Director General of the Bureau, who shall be its ex officio Chairman; and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of members, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee constituted under sub-section (1) shall perform, exercise and discharge`
  line `such functions, powers and duties of the Bureau, as may be delegated to it by the Governing Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2911)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Advisory Committees of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2911&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any regulations made in this behalf, the`
  line `Governing Council may, from time to time and as and when it is considered necessary, constitute the`
  line `following Advisory Committees for the efficient discharge of the functions of the Bureau, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) Finance Advisory Committee;`
  line
  line `(b) Conformity Assessment Advisory Committee;`
  line
  line `(c) Standards Advisory Committee;`
  line
  line `(d) Testing and Calibration Advisory Committee; and`
  line
  line `(e) such number of other committees as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Each Advisory Committee shall consist of a Chairman and such other members as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2912)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate act or proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2912&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceedings of the Governing`
  line `Council, under section 3 shall be invalid merely by reason of—`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of the Governing Council; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Governing Council; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Governing Council not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2913)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Director General.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2913&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint a Director General of the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the Director General of the Bureau shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the general superintendence and control of the Governing Council, the Director General`
  line `of the Bureau shall be the Chief Executive Authority of the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director General of the Bureau shall exercise and discharge such of the powers and duties of`
  line `the Bureau as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) The Director General may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to any officer of the`
  line `Bureau subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of his powers and`
  line `functions as are assigned to him under the regulations or are delegated to him by the Governing Council,`
  line `as he may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2914)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Officers and employees of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2914&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau may appoint such other officers and`
  line `employees as it considers necessary for the efficient discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of officers and employees of the Bureau appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be such as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2915)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Powers and functions of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2915&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The powers and duties as may be assigned to the Bureau`
  line `under this Act shall be exercised and performed by the Governing Council and, in particular, such powers`
  line `may include the power to—`
  line
  line `(a) establish branches, offices or agencies in India or outside;`
  line
  line `(b) recognise, on reciprocal basis or otherwise, with the prior approval of the Central`
  line `Government, the mark of any international body or institution, on such terms and conditions as may`
  line `be mutually agreed upon by the Bureau in relation to any goods, article, process, system or service at`
  line `par with the Standard Mark for such goods, article, process, system or service;`
  line
  line `(c) seek recognition of the Bureau and of the Indian Standards outside India on such terms and`
  line `conditions as may be mutually agreed upon by the Bureau with any corresponding institution or`
  line `organisation in any country or with any international organisation;`
  line
  line `(d) enter into and search places, premises or vehicles, and inspect and seize goods or articles and`
  line `documents to enforce the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) provide services to manufacturers and consumers of goods or articles or processes for`
  line `compliances of standards on such terms and conditions as may be mutually agreed upon;`
  line
  line `(f) provide training services in relation to quality management, standards, conformity assessment,`
  line `laboratory testing and calibration, and any other related areas;`
  line
  line `(g) publish Indian Standards and sell such publications and publications of international bodies;`
  line
  line `(h) authorise agencies in India or outside India for carrying out any or all activities of the Bureau`
  line `and such other purposes as may be necessary on such terms and conditions as it deems fit;`
  line
  line `(i) obtain membership in regional, international and foreign bodies having objects similar to that`
  line `of the Bureau and participate in international standards setting process;`
  line
  line `(j) undertake testing of samples for purposes other than for conformity assessment; and`
  line
  line `(k) undertake activities relating to legal metrology.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bureau shall take all necessary steps for promotion, monitoring and management of the`
  line `quality of goods, articles, processes, systems and services, as may be necessary, to protect the interests of`
  line `consumers and various other stake holders which may include the following namely: —`
  line
  line `(a) carrying out market surveillance or survey of any goods, article, process, system or service to`
  line `monitor their quality and publish findings of such surveillance or surveys;`
  line
  line `(b) promotion of quality in connection with any goods, article, process, system or service by`
  line `creating awareness among the consumers and the industry and educate them about quality and`
  line `standards in connection with any goods, article, process, system and service;`
  line
  line `(c) promotion of safety in connection with any goods, article, process, system or service;`
  line
  line `(d) identification of any goods, articles, process, system or service for which there is a need to`
  line `establish a new Indian Standard, or to revise an existing Indian Standard;`
  line
  line `(e) promoting the use of Indian Standards;`
  line
  line `(f) recognising or accrediting any institution in India or outside which is engaged in conformity`
  line `certification and inspection of any goods, article, process, system or service or of testing laboratories;`
  line
  line `(g) coordination and promotion of activities of any association of manufacturers or consumers or`
  line `any other body in relation to improvement in the quality or in the implementation of any quality`
  line `assurance activities in relation to any goods, article, process, system or service; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other functions as may be necessary for promotion, monitoring and management of the`
  line `quality of goods, articles, processes, systems and services and to protect the interests of consumers`
  line `and other stake holders.`
  line
  line `(3) The Bureau shall perform its functions under this section through the Governing Council in`
  line `accordance with the direction and subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (2916)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Indian Standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2916&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The standards established by the Bureau shall be the Indian Standards.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bureau may--`
  line
  line `(a) establish, publish, review and promote the Indian Standard, in relation to any goods, article,`
  line `process, system or service in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) adopt as Indian Standard, any standard, established by any other Institution in India or`
  line `elsewhere, in relation to any goods, article, process, system or service in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(c) recognise or accredit any institution in India or outside which is engaged in standardisation;`
  line
  line `(d) undertake, support and promote such research as may be necessary for formulation of Indian`
  line Standards.
  line
  line `(3) The Bureau, for the purpose of this section, shall constitute, as and when considered necessary, such number of technical committees of experts for the formulation of standards in respect of goods,`
  line `articles, processes, systems or services, as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) The Indian Standard shall be notified and remain valid till withdrawn by the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, the copyright in an Indian Standard or any`
  line `other publication of the Bureau shall vest in the Bureau.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (2917)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Prohibition to publish, reproduce or record without authorisation by Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2917&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `individual shall, without the authorisation of the Bureau, in any manner or form, publish, reproduce or`
  line `record any Indian Standard or part thereof, or any other publication of the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall issue a document that creates, or may create the impression that it is or contains`
  line `an Indian Standard, as contemplated in this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall prevent any individual from making a copy of Indian`
  line `Standard for his personal use.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (2918)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Conformity Assessment scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2918&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau may notify a specific or different conformity`
  line `assessment scheme for any goods, article, process, system or service or for a group of goods, articles,`
  line `processes, systems or services, as the case may be, with respect to any Indian Standard or any other`
  line `standard in a manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The Bureau may establish a Standard Mark in relation to each of its conformity assessment`
  line `schemes, which shall be of such design and contain such particulars as may be specified by regulations to`
  line `represent a particular standard.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (2919)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Grant of licence or certificate of conformity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2919&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person may apply for grant of licence or`
  line `certificate of conformity, as the case may be, if the goods, article, process, system or service conforms to`
  line `an Indian Standard.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any goods, article, process, system or service conforms to a standard, the Director General`
  line `may, by an order, grant—`
  line
  line `(a) a certificate of conformity in a manner as may be specified by regulations; or`
  line
  line `(b) a licence to use or apply a Standard Mark in a manner as may be specified by regulations,`
  line
  line `subject to such conditions and on payment of such fees, including late fee or fine, before or during the`
  line `operation of the certificate of conformity or licence, and as determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) While granting a certificate of conformity or licence to use a Standard Mark, the Bureau may, by`
  line `order, specify the marking and labelling requirements that shall necessarily be affixed as may be specified`
  line `from time to time.`
  line
  line `(4) The Bureau may establish, maintain or recognise testing laboratories for the purposes of`
  line `conformity assessment and quality assurance and for such other purposes as may be required for carrying`
  line `out its functions.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (2920)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Certification of Standard Mark of jewellers and sellers of certain specified goods or articles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2920&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government, after consulting the Bureau, may notify precious metal articles or`
  line `other goods or articles as it may consider necessary, to be marked with a Hallmark or Standard Mark, as`
  line `the case may be, in a manner as specified in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The goods or articles notified in sub-section (1) may be sold through retail outlets certified by the`
  line `Bureau after such goods or articles have been assessed for conformity to the relevant standard by testing`
  line `and marking centre, recognised by the Bureau and marked with Hallmark or Standard Mark, as the case`
  line `may be, as specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, after consulting the Bureau, by an order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make it compulsory for the sellers of goods or article notified under sub-section (1) to be sold`
  line `only through certified sales outlets fulfilling such conditions as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) The Bureau may, by an order, grant, renew, suspend or cancel certification of Standard Mark or`
  line `Hallmark of a jeweller or any other seller for sale of goods or articles notified under sub-section (1) in`
  line `such manner as may be determined by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) The Bureau may establish, maintain and recognise testing and marking centres, including assaying`
  line `and hallmarking centres, for conformity assessment and application of Standard Mark, including`
  line `Hallmark, on goods or articles notified under sub-section (1), in a manner as may be specified by`
  line regulations.
  line
  line `(6) No testing and marking centre or assaying and hallmarking centre, other than the recognised by`
  line `the Bureau, shall with respect to goods or articles notified under sub-section (1), use, affix, emboss,`
  line `engrave, print or apply in any manner the Standard Mark, including the Hallmark, or colourable imitation`
  line `thereof, on any goods or article; and make any claim in relation to the use and application of a Standard`
  line `Mark, including the Hallmark, through advertisements, sales promotion leaflets, price lists or the like.`
  line
  line `(7) Every recognised testing and marking centre, including assaying and hallmarking centre, shall use`
  line `or apply Standard Mark on good or articles notified under sub-section (1), including Hallmark on`
  line `precious metal articles, after accurately determining the conformity of the same in a manner as may be`
  line specified.
  line
  line `(8) No recognised testing and marking centre, including assaying and hallmarking centre, shall,`
  line `notwithstanding that it has been recognised under sub-section (5), use or apply in relation to any goods or`
  line `article notified under sub-section (1) a Standard Mark, including Hallmark, or any colourable imitation`
  line `thereof, unless such goods or article conforms to the relevant standard.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (2921)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Prohibition to import, sell, exhibit, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2921&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall import, distribute, sell, store or`
  line `exhibit for sale, any goods or article under sub-section (1) of section 14, except under certification from`
  line `the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(2) No person, other than that certified by the Bureau, shall sell or display or offer to sell goods or`
  line `articles that are notified under sub-section (3) of section 14 and marked with the Standard Mark,`
  line `including Hallmark and claim in relation to the Standard Mark, including Hallmark, through`
  line `advertisements, sales promotion leaflets, price lists or the like.`
  line
  line `(3) No certified jeweller or seller shall sell or display or offer to sell any notified goods or articles,`
  line `notwithstanding that he has been granted certification, with the Standard Mark, including Hallmark, or`
  line `any colourable imitation thereof, unless such goods or article is marked with a Standard Mark or`
  line `Hallmark, in a manner as may be specified by regulations, and unless such goods or article conforms to`
  line `the relevant standard.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (2922)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Central Government to direct compulsory use of Standard Mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2922&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central`
  line `Government is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest or for the`
  line `protection of human, animal or plant health, safety of the environment, or prevention of unfair trade`
  line `practices, or national security, it may, after consulting the Bureau, by an order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, notify—`
  line
  line `(a) goods or article of any scheduled industry, process, system or service; or`
  line
  line `(b) essential requirements to which such goods, article, process, system or service,`
  line
  line `which shall conform to a standard and direct the use of the Standard Mark under a licence or certificate of`
  line `conformity as compulsory on such goods, article, process, system or service.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this sub-section,—`
  line
  line `(i) the expression "scheduled industry" shall have the meaning assigned to it in the Industries`
  line `(Development and Regulation) Act, 1951 (65 of 1951);`
  line
  line `(ii) it is hereby clarified that essential requirements are requirements, expressed in terms of the`
  line `parameters to be achieved or requirements of standard in technical terms that effectively ensure that`
  line `any goods, article, process, system or service meet the objective of health, safety and environment.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by an order authorise Bureau or any other agency having necessary`
  line `accreditation or recognition and valid approval to certify and enforce conformity to the relevant standard`
  line `or prescribed essential requirements under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (2923)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Prohibition to manufacture, sell, etc., certain goods without Standard Mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2923&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person`
  line `shall manufacture, import, distribute, sell, hire, lease, store or exhibit for sale any such goods, article,`
  line `process, system or service under sub-section (1) of section 16—`
  line
  line `(a) without a Standard Mark, except under a valid licence; or`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding that he has been granted a license, apply a Standard Mark, unless such goods,`
  line `article, process, system or service conforms to the relevant standard or prescribed essential`
  line requirements.
  line
  line `(2) No person shall make a public claim, through advertisements, sales promotion leaflets, price lists`
  line `or the like, that his goods, article, process, system or service conforms to an Indian standard or make such`
  line `a declaration on the goods or article, without having a valid certificate of conformity or licence from the`
  line `Bureau or any other authority approved by the Central Government under sub-section (2) of section 16.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall use or apply or purport to use or apply in any manner, in the manufacture,`
  line `distribution, sale, hire, lease or exhibit or offer for sale of any goods, article, process, system or service, or`
  line `in the title of any patent or in any trade mark or design, a Standard Mark or any colourable imitation`
  line `thereof, except under a valid licence from the Bureau.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (2924)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Obligations of licence holder, seller, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2924&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The licence holder shall, at all times, remain`
  line `responsible for conformance of the goods, articles, processes, systems or services carrying the Standard`
  line Mark.
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the responsibility of the distributor or the seller, as the case may be, to ensure that`
  line `goods, articles, processes, systems or services carrying the Standard Mark are purchased from certified`
  line `body or licence holder.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be the responsibility of the seller before the goods or article is sold or offered to be sold or`
  line `exhibited or offered for sale to ensure that—`
  line
  line `(a) goods, articles, processes, systems or services carrying the Standard Mark bear the requisite`
  line `labels and marking details, as specified by the Bureau from time to time;`
  line
  line `(b) the marking and labelling requirements on the product or covering is displayed in a manner`
  line `that has been specified by the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(4) Every certified body or licence holder shall supply to the Bureau with such information and with`
  line `such samples of any material or substance used in relation to any goods, article, process, system or`
  line `service, as the case may be, as the Bureau may require for monitoring its quality and for the recovery of`
  line `the fee as may be prescribed in the certificate of conformity or the licence.`
  line
  line `(5) (a) The Bureau may make such inspection and take such samples of any material or substance as`
  line `may be necessary to see whether any goods, article, process, system or service, in relation to which a`
  line `Standard Mark has been used, conforms to the requirements of the relevant standard or whether the`
  line `Standard Mark has been properly used in relation to any goods, article, process, system or service with or`
  line `without a licence.`
  line
  line `(b) The Bureau may publicise the results of its findings and the directions given in pursuance`
  line thereof.
  line
  line `(6) If the Bureau is satisfied under the provisions of sub-sections (4) and (5) that the goods, articles,`
  line `processes, systems or services in relation to which a Standard Mark has been used do not conform to the`
  line `requirements of the relevant standard, the Bureau may direct the certified body or licence holder or his`
  line `representative to stop the supply and sale of non-conforming goods or articles and recall the nonconforming`
  line `goods or articles that have already been supplied or offered for sale and bear such mark from`
  line `the market or any such place from where they are likely to be offered for sale or prohibit to provide the`
  line service.
  line
  line `(7) Where a certified body or licence holder or his representative has sold goods, articles, processes,`
  line `system or services, which bear a Standard Mark or any colourable imitation thereof, which do not`
  line `conform to the relevant standard, the Bureau shall direct the certified body or licence holder or his`
  line `representative to—`
  line
  line `(a) repair or replace or reprocess the standard marked goods, article, process, system or service in`
  line `a manner as may be specified; or`
  line
  line `(b) pay compensation to the consumer as may be prescribed by the Bureau; or`
  line
  line `(c) be liable for the injury caused by non-conforming goods or article, which bears a Standard`
  line `Mark, as per the provisions of section 31.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (2925)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Financial Management of Bureau of Indian Standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2925&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after`
  line `due appropriation made by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Bureau grants and loans of such`
  line `sums of money as the Government may consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (2926)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Fund of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2926&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be constituted a fund to be called the Bureau of Indian`
  line `Standards fund and there shall be credited thereto—`
  line
  line `(a) any grants and loans made to the Bureau by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and charges received by the Bureau under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) all fines received by the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(d) all sums received by the Bureau from such other sources as may be decided upon by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The fund shall be applied for meeting—`
  line
  line `(a) the salary, allowances and other remuneration of the members, Director General, officers and`
  line `other employees of the Bureau;`
  line
  line `(b) expenses of the Bureau in the discharge of its functions under the Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) expenses on objects and for purposes authorised by this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the fines received in clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall be used for consumer awareness,`
  line `consumer protection and promotion of quality of goods, articles, processes, system or services in the`
  line country.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (2927)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Borrowing powers of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2927&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau may, with the consent of the Central`
  line `Government or in accordance with the terms of any general or special authority given to it by the Central`
  line `Government, borrow money from any source as it may deem fit for discharging all or any of its functions`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may guarantee in such manner as it thinks fit, the repayment of the`
  line `principal and the payment of interest thereon with respect to the loans borrowed by Bureau under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (2928)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2928&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Bureau shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year as may`
  line `be prescribed, its budget for the next financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of the`
  line `Bureau and forward the same to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (2929)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2929&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial`
  line `year as may be prescribed, its annual report, giving a full account of its activities during the previous`
  line `financial year, and submit a copy thereof to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall cause the annual report to be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `received, before each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (2930)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2930&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts, in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Bureau shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him and any expenditure incurred in connection with such audit`
  line `shall be payable by the Bureau to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Bureau shall have the same rights and privileges and the authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally has in connection`
  line `with the audit of Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the production of`
  line `books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any office of the`
  line Bureau.
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Bureau as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (2931)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power of Central Government to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2931&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the foregoing`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Bureau shall, in the exercise of its powers or the performance of its functions`
  line `under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may give in`
  line `writing to it from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Bureau shall, as far as practicable, be given an opportunity to express its views`
  line `before any direction is given under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may take such other action as may be necessary for the promotion,`
  line `monitoring and management of quality of goods, articles, processes, systems and services and to protect`
  line `the interests of consumers and various other stakeholders and notify any other goods, articles, processes,`
  line `systems and services for the purpose of sub-section (1) of section 16.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (2932)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Restriction on use of name of Bureau and Indian Standard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2932&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, with a view`
  line `to deceive or likely to deceive the public, use without the previous permission of the Bureau, —`
  line
  line `(a) any name which so nearly resembles the name of the Bureau as to deceive or likely to deceive`
  line `the public or the name which contains the expression "Indian Standard" or any abbreviation`
  line `thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) any title of any patent or mark or trade mark or design, in relation to any goods, article,`
  line `process, system or service, containing the expressions "Indian Standard" or "Indian Standard`
  line `Specification" or any abbreviation of such expressions.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, no registering`
  line `authority shall—`
  line
  line `(a) register any company, firm or other body of persons which bears any name or mark; or`
  line
  line `(b) register a trade mark or design which bears any name or mark; or`
  line
  line `(c) grant a patent, in respect of an invention, which bears a title containing any name or mark,`
  line
  line `if the use of such name or mark is in contravention of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) If any question arises before a registering authority whether the use of any name or mark is in`
  line `contravention of sub-section (1), the registering authority may refer the question to the Central`
  line `Government whose decision thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (2933)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Appointment and powers of certification officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2933&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau may appoint as many`
  line `certification officers as may be necessary for the purpose of inspection whether any goods, article,`
  line `process, system or service in relation to which the Standard Mark has been used conforms to the relevant`
  line `standard or whether the Standard Mark has been properly used in relation to any goods, article, process,`
  line `system or service with or without licence, and for performing such other functions as may be assigned to`
  line them.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any rules made under this Act, a certification officer shall have power to—`
  line
  line `(a) inspect any operation carried on in connection with any goods, article, process, system or`
  line `service in relation to which the Standard Mark has been used; and`
  line
  line `(b) take samples of any goods or article or of any material or substance used in any goods, article,`
  line `process, system or service, in relation to which the Standard Mark has been used.`
  line
  line `(3) Every certification officer shall be furnished by the Bureau with a certificate of appointment as a`
  line `certification officer, and the certificate shall, on demand, be produced by the certification officer.`
  line
  line `(4) Every certified body or licence holder shall—`
  line
  line `(a) provide reasonable facilities to certification officer to enable him to discharge the duties`
  line `imposed on him;`
  line
  line `(b) inform certification officer or the Bureau of any change in the conditions which were declared`
  line `or verified by the certification officer or the Bureau at the time of grant of certificate of conformity or`
  line licence.
  line
  line `(5) Any information obtained by a certification officer or the Bureau from any statement made or`
  line `information supplied or any evidence given or from inspection made under the provisions of this Act shall`
  line `be treated as confidential:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing shall apply to the disclosure of any information for the purpose of prosecution`
  line `and protection of interest of consumers`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (2934)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2934&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the certification officer has reason to believe that any`
  line `goods or articles, process, system or service in relation to which the contravention of section 11 or`
  line `sub-sections (6) or (8) of section 14 or section 15 or section 17 has taken place are secreted in any place,`
  line `premises or vehicle, he may enter into and search such place, premises or vehicle for such goods or`
  line `articles, process, system or service, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, as a result of any search made under sub-section (1), any goods or article, process, system`
  line `or service has been found in relation to which contravention of section 11 or sub-sections (6) or (8) of`
  line `section 14 or section 15 or section 17 has taken place, the certification officer may seize such goods or`
  line `article and other material and documents which, in his opinion will be useful for, or relevant to any`
  line `proceeding under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not practicable to seize any such goods or article or material or document,`
  line `the certification officer may serve on the owner an order that he shall not remove, part with, or otherwise`
  line `deal with, the goods or article or material or document except with the previous permission of the`
  line `certification officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The provision of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to searches and`
  line `seizures shall, so far as may be, apply to every search or seizure made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (2935)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Penalty for contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2935&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who contravenes the provisions of section 11 or`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 26 shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who contravenes the provisions of sub-sections (6) or (8) of section 14 or section 15`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with fine which shall`
  line `not be less than one lakh rupees, but may extend up to five times the value of goods or articles produced`
  line `or sold or offered to be sold or affixed or applied with a Standard Mark including Hallmark, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the value of goods or articles produced or sold or offered to be sold cannot be`
  line `determined, it shall be presumed that one year's production was in such contravention and the annual`
  line `turnover in the previous financial year shall be taken as the value of goods or articles for such`
  line contravention.
  line
  line `(3) Any person who contravenes the provisions of section 17 shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend up to two years or with fine which shall not be less than two lakh rupees for`
  line `the first contravention and not be less than five lakh rupees for the second and subsequent contraventions,`
  line `but may extend up to ten times the value of goods or articles produced or sold or offered to be sold or`
  line `affixed or applied with a Standard Mark, including Hallmark, or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the value of goods or articles produced or sold or offered to be sold cannot be`
  line `determined, it shall be presumed that one year's production was in such contravention and the annual`
  line `turnover in the previous financial year shall be taken as the value of goods or articles for such`
  line contravention.
  line
  line `(4) The offence under sub-section (3) shall be cognizable.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (2936)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2936&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a company,`
  line `every director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company who, at the time the offence was`
  line `committed, was in charge of and was responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the`
  line `company, or authorised representative of the company as well as the company, shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly, irrespective of`
  line `the fact that the offence has been committed with or without the consent or connivance of, or is`
  line `attributable to any neglect on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company,`
  line `or authorised representative of the company.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section,—`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (2937)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Compensation for non-conforming goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2937&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Where a holder of licence or certificate of`
  line `conformity or his representative has sold any goods, article, process, system or service, which bears a`
  line `Standard Mark not conforming to the relevant standard, or with colourable imitation, the certified body or`
  line `licence holder or his representative shall be liable to compensate the consumer for the injury caused by`
  line `such non-conforming goods, article, process, system or service in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (2938)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Cognizance of offence by courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2938&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a`
  line `Judicial Magistrate of the first class, specially empowered in this behalf, shall try any offence punishable`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this Act save on a complaint`
  line `made by—`
  line
  line `(a) or under the authority of the Bureau; or`
  line
  line `(b) any police officer, not below the rank of deputy superintendent of police or equivalent; or`
  line
  line `(c) any authority notified under sub-section (2) of section 16; or`
  line
  line `(d) any officer empowered under the authority of the Government; or`
  line
  line `(e) any consumer; or`
  line
  line `(f) any association.`
  line
  line `(3) Any police officer not below the rank of deputy superintendent of police or equivalent, may, if he`
  line `is satisfied that any of the offences referred to in sub-section (3) of section 29 has been, is being, or is`
  line `likely to be, committed, search and seize without warrant, the goods, die, block, machine, plate, other`
  line `instruments or things involved in committing the offence, wherever found, and all the articles so seized`
  line `shall, as soon as practicable, be produced before a Magistrate as prescribed under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The court may direct that any property in respect of which the contravention has taken place shall`
  line `be forfeited to the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(5) The court may direct that any fine, in whole or any part thereof, payable under the provisions of`
  line `this Act, shall be payable to the Bureau.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (2939)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Compounding of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2939&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence committed for the first time, punishable under this Act, not`
  line `being an offence punishable with imprisonment only, or with imprisonment and also with fine, may,`
  line `either before or after the institution of any prosecution, be compounded by an officer so authorised by the`
  line `Director General, in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the sum so specified shall not in any case exceed the maximum amount of the fine`
  line `which may be imposed under section 29 for the offence so compounded; and any second or subsequent`
  line `offence committed after the expiry of a period of three years from the date on which the offence was`
  line `previously compounded shall be deemed to be an offence committed for the first time.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer referred to in sub-section (1) shall exercise the powers to compound an offence,`
  line `subject to the direction, control and supervision of the Bureau.`
  line
  line `(3) Every application for the compounding of an offence shall be made in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) Where any offence is compounded before the institution of any prosecution, no prosecution shall`
  line `be instituted in relation to such offence against the offender in relation to whom the offence is so`
  line compounded.
  line
  line `(5) Where the composition of any offence is made after the institution of any prosecution, such`
  line `composition shall be brought to the notice of the court in which the prosecution is pending in writing by`
  line `the officer referred to in sub-section (1), and on such notice of the composition of the offence being given`
  line `and its acceptance by the court, the person against whom the offence is so compounded shall be`
  line discharged.
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (2940)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2940&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made under section 13 or sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 14 or section 17 of this Act may prefer an appeal to Director General of the Bureau within such`
  line `period as prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall be admitted if it is preferred after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor if the`
  line `appellant satisfies the Director General that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within`
  line `the prescribed period.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal made under this section shall be made in such form and shall be accompanied by a`
  line `copy of the order appealed against and by such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The procedure for disposing of an appeal shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that before disposing of an appeal, the appellant shall be given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) The Director General may suo motu or on an application made in the manner prescribed review`
  line `the order passed by any officer to whom the power has been delegated by him.`
  line
  line `(6) Any person aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (5) may prefer an`
  line `appeal to the Central Government having administrative control of the Bureau within such period as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (2941)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Members, officers and employees of Bureau to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2941&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `All members, officers`
  line `and other employees of the Bureau shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (2942)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2942&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government or any officer of the Government or any member, officer or other employee of`
  line `the Bureau for anything which is in done or intended to be done in good faith under this Act or the rules`
  line `or regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (2943)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments of Bureau.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2943&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of, and`
  line `all other instruments issued by, the Bureau shall be authenticated by the signature of such officer or`
  line `officers as may be authorised by the Bureau in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (2944)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2944&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (2945)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2945&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `The Executive Committee may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and`
  line `the rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (2946)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2946&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made`
  line `under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it`
  line `is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the`
  line `successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (2947)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Act not to affect operation of certain Acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2947&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall affect the operation of the`
  line `Agricultural Produce (Grading and Marking) Act, 1937 (1 of 1937), or the Drugs and Cosmetics`
  line `Act, 1940 (23 of 1940), or any other law for the time being in force, which deals with any standardisation`
  line `or quality control of any goods, article, process, system or service.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (2948)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2948&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (2949)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370&sectionId=2949&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00008_201611_1517807328370
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Bureau of Indian Standards Act, 1986 (63 of 1986), is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken or purported to have done or`
  line `taken including any rule, regulation, notification, scheme, specification, Indian Standard, Standard Mark,`
  line `inspection order or notice made, issued or adopted, or any appointment, or declaration made or any`
  line `licence, permission, authorisation or exemption granted or any document or instrument executed or`
  line `direction given or any proceedings taken or any penalty or fine imposed under the Act hereby repealed`
  line `shall, insofar as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or`
  line `taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of particular matters in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice or affect the`
  line `general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), with regard to the effect of`
  line repeal.
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
